# Daily startup routine (smol-portal / PorTAL)

Run once at the start of each working day, before touching PorTAL code. Two quick
checks keep us aligned with the foundation (**smolvm**) and the reference (Ramp's
**portallib**). Log observations in the private watch-logs under
`/Users/nicky/Documents/smolvm-notes/`, not in public docs.

## 1. Pull latest smolvm (the foundation)

smolvm is where we catch bugs and submit upstream; PorTAL validation depends on
its current behaviour. Sync the local checkout **safely** (never a blind `git pull`):

```bash
cd /Users/nicky/Documents/smolvm
git fetch upstream --tags
git rev-list --left-right --count main...upstream/main   # behind <tab> ahead
git tag --sort=-creatordate | head -4                    # any new release?
git merge --ff-only upstream/main                         # only if 0 ahead
```

- `upstream` = `smol-machines/smolvm`; `origin` = fork `NickyHeC/smolvm`.
- Fast-forward `main` only when **0 ahead** of `upstream/main`. If `main` has
  local commits ahead (or a rebase is needed), **stop and report** — don't force.
- Building? also `git submodule update --init --recursive` (libkrun / libkrunfw).

**Escalate on a new release tag (e.g. v1.6.0):**
- The CUDA **shim build tag must match the release** — rebuild shims for the new
  tag before any Lambda run (see the smolvm-interop rule).
- Re-validate PorTAL against the new version; if the working minimum changes,
  update `smol-portal/SPEC.md` ("smolvm ≥ x"), `examples/smolvm/`, and the runbook.
- Note CUDA-relevant upstream changes (new files/branches under `src/` or
  `crates/smolvm-cuda*`, e.g. `cuda_daemon.rs`, `cuda-fork-*`).
- Log the version delta + actions in `smolvm-notes/watches/smolvm-version-watch.md`.

## 2. Check `ramp-public/portallib` (the reference)

Ramp's public PorTAL reference is our ground truth for the method. Check at most
once/day:

```bash
gh repo view ramp-public/portallib
gh api repos/ramp-public/portallib/commits \
  --jq '.[] | "\(.commit.author.date)  \(.sha[0:7])  \(.commit.message|split("\n")[0])"' | head
gh api repos/ramp-public/portallib/tags --jq '.[].name'
gh api "repos/ramp-public/portallib/issues?state=all" --jq '.[] | "#\(.number) \(.state) \(.title)"'
```

- Diff against the newest entry in `smolvm-notes/watches/portallib-watch.md`; if nothing
  changed, don't re-log.
- **Escalate when** issue #1 "Add portallib v0.1 alpha" merges / code lands, a
  release/tag appears, PyPI/HF publishes, or paper-scale (Qwen3-8B / Gemma-3-4B)
  artifacts publish. Then diff their trainer / refitter / evaluator against our
  `pipeline/portal` and update ROADMAP Phase A2.
